commitMessage:"Switch to fork of tzdb\n\nUsing 2021b would mean that 9 timezones would be lost to Joda-Time users

commitMessage:"Fix deadlock due to DateTimeZone.UTC

Referencing DateTimeZone and FixedDateTimeZone from two
threads at startup could deadlock
Add package scoped UTCDateTimeZone class to avoid this

DateTimeZone.UTC has changed implementation type
It used to be a FixedDateTimeZone
Now it is a UTCDateTimeZone
This avoids a potential deadlock scenario
Serialization is unaffected
This change will only be observable if you cast the
UTC constant to FixedDateTimeZone
Fixes #171
"

commitMessage:"Simplified Cache Lookup of GJChronologies.

This commit replaces the cache lookup using only the zone and then
iterating over the ArrayList donating possible candidates with a single
cache access. For this purpose a temporary cache key is instantiated.

In the cache hit case this code will produce a temporary GJCacheKey
object and then return the GJChronology
column6: an ArrayList iteration was performed\nand an Instant was checked for equality.\n"

column3: commitMessage:"Avoid locking as much as possible related to Chronology caching.\n\nAll Chronology classes used synchronising on the chronology cache
column4:
which
leads to degraded performance once the cache has a high hit ratio.
This patch narrows the synchronised path onto the updating part by using
ConcurrentHashMap. The remaining synchronisation ensures identity and
prevents lost updates
column5: which might be acceptable but are not strictly\nbackwards compatible.\n"

  Also add tests whether parsing correctly throws an exception
    when a string has rendundant separators
    AND seperators for the language are not empty.

  and Hajime Senuma (author of this commit).
